    "content": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Dynamic Snapping"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Object Snapping"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "The S2M CENTER provides a special kind of cursor snap in addition to the typical grid snap. This allows the cursor to automatically snap to different hot-points on or adjacent to an object; for example, end-points, mid-points, center-points, and intersections. These locations are commonly referenced when creating or editing geometry. For most functions, the cursor will also snap to the origin of the object."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "For example, you may want to create a line that is connected to the end of an arc. Start creating the line by locating the endpoint of the arc. When located, a round  hot-point  marker appears on the arc endpoint."
        },
        {
            "type": "link",
            "data": {
                "text": "hot-point",
                "uuid": "8f613db7-aaad-442d-8a76-4ab1a601c5d7",
                "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "image767.gif",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Click the hot-point marker to start the line there. The start of the line snaps precisely to the end of the arc, connecting these objects end-to-end."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "You can choose what types of positions and conditions will automatically be located by enabling or disabling options in  Preferences | Tools Tab ."
        },
        {
            "type": "link",
            "data": {
                "text": "Preferences | Tools Tab",
                "uuid": "a6c6d306-c8da-4df8-8440-33f2f24a9c1d",
                "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "General Snapping Shortcut Keys"
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "alt_key.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Ignores snap to Grid and Points, and leaves the Smart-Lines angle snap on."
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "shift_key.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Activates the \"full grid snap\" mode, forcing snap to the Grid over a position just aligned with a Point."
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "ctrl_key.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Completely ignores snap, including Smart-Lines."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "+"
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "ctrl_key.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "shift_key.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Dynamic Snapping"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Solid also has the ability to Snap Dynamically (also known as Assumptive Snapping). When you are in line with a Snap Point on another Object within the Drawing space the S2M CENTER will project that position to your location. When this projection along with the associated  hot-point marker  is displayed you can be assured that the Object will be placed in-line with that Objects Snap Point."
        },
        {
            "type": "link",
            "data": {
                "text": "hot-point marker",
                "uuid": "8f613db7-aaad-442d-8a76-4ab1a601c5d7",
                "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "For Example you would like to draw two line Parallel to each other. After drawing the first line simply move your cursor in-line with the first lines Start Point and you will see a Snap Line projection assuring you they are in-line."
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "image768.gif",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "Hot-point Markers"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "When the cursor moves over a valid snap location, the located position displays with a hot-point marker and a special cursor appears to identify the type of location."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "data": "The system will not display a hot-point marker for a particular location type if it is disabled in  Preferences | Tools Tab ."
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "data": "Information.png",
            "description": "[Placeholder for AI-generated description]"
        },
        {
